+ set +x
This script builds and installs the P4_16 (and also P4_14)
compiler, and the behavioral-model software packet forwarding
program, that can behave as just about any legal P4 program.

It is regularly tested on freshly installed versions of these systems:
    Ubuntu 20.04
    Ubuntu 22.04
    Ubuntu 24.04
with all Ubuntu software updates as of the date of testing.  See
this directory for log files recording the last date this script
was tested on its supported operating systems:

    https://github.com/jafingerhut/p4-guide/tree/master/bin/output

The files installed by this script consume about 25 GB of disk space.

On a 2019 MacBook Pro with a decent speed Internet connection
and an SSD drive, running Ubuntu Linux in a VirtualBox VM, it
took about 2 hours.

Versions of software that will be installed by this script:

+ gRPC: github.com/google/grpc.git v1.51.1
+ PI: github.com/p4lang/PI latest version
+ behavioral-model: github.com/p4lang/behavioral-model latest version
  which, as of 2023-Sep-22, also installs these things:
  + thrift version 0.16.0
  + nanomsg version 1.0.0
  + nnpy latest version available via 'pip install'
+ p4c: github.com/p4lang/p4c latest version
+ ptf: github.com/p4lang/ptf latest version
+ tutorials: github.com/p4lang/tutorials latest version
+ Mininet: github.com/mininet/mininet latest version as of 2024-Sep-18
+ Python packages: protobuf 4.21.12, grpcio - a recent version auto-selected by pip3
+ Python packages: scapy (2.5.0), psutil, crcmod

Note that anything installed as 'the latest version' can change
its precise contents from one run of this script to another.
That is an intentional property of this script -- to get the
latest version of that software.  If you want particular
versions that are not the latest, you can modify this script by
adding 'git checkout <tag>' and/or 'git checkout <commit-sha>'
command at the appropriate places.

If you ever happen to want to link against installed libraries
in a given directory, LIBDIR, you must either use libtool, and
specify the full pathname of the library, or use the '-LLIBDIR'
flag during linking and do at least one of the following:
   - add LIBDIR to the 'LD_LIBRARY_PATH' environment variable
     during execution
   - add LIBDIR to the 'LD_RUN_PATH' environment variable
     during linking
   - use the '-Wl,-rpath -Wl,LIBDIR' linker flag
   - have your system administrator add LIBDIR to '/etc/ld.so.conf'

See any operating system documentation about shared libraries for
more information, such as the ld(1) and ld.so(8) manual pages.

commit 82094bdcda0a1456c9b884eebc4a50385b1dd120
Author: Andy Fingerhut <andy_fingerhut@alum.wustl.edu>
Date:   Tue Sep 3 13:45:18 2024 -0400

    Make a Merge() call allow not-yet-recognized new fields in P4Info files (#132)
    
    Make a Merge() call allow not-yet-recognized new fields in P4Info files
    This is helpful when p4c adds new P4Info fields to the P4Info files it
    generates, but the consumers have not yet all been updated to
    recognize them.  The most recent example of this in 2024-Aug is the
    initial_default_action field of Table messages.
    
    Signed-off-by: Andy Fingerhut <andy_fingerhut@alum.wustl.edu>
